🔴 **Design Concern** — `review/arm-alertsmanagement-node.api.md:618`
```ts
export interface ProxyResource_1 {
    readonly id?: string;
    readonly name?: string;
    readonly type?: string;
}
```
Both `ProxyResource` (which extends `Resource`) and `ProxyResource_1` are exported. The `_1` suffix is auto-generated to resolve a name collision between two distinct models mapped to the same TypeSpec name, which is a sign of duplicated or ambiguously-named models in the spec.

**Fix:** Prepare a PR to use `@clientName` in the spec repo's TypeSpec to give one of the two models a distinct, meaningful name (e.g., `BasicProxyResource`), then trigger SDK regeneration.
